V 332
instead of calling isnan(), prevent the division by zero altogether.  division by zero can crash on non-ieee systems and be configured to throw an exception even on modern systems (which will abort the application).  the intent is to just skip perpedicular faces, so using RT_DOT_TOL should give more consistent repeatable behavior.
